          <p>
            God of beggers and thieves. Soketh is the god of the streets, the god of the people. He teaches his followers to be cunning, to be quick, to be the shadow. Soketh is often worshiped by the poor and the downtrodden, those who have nothing to lose but the need and ambition to take.
            Followers of Soketh believe that theivery is alright, only those who are irresponsible with their wealth have it taken from them.
            <br>
            Soketh is responsible for the domains of trickery and life.
            <br>
            His symbol is a beggers cup.
      
            <br>
            Soketh is often depicted as a tall young man in a gray hood with 3 beggers cups from his waist
